{
    "identity": "nprot-6413",
    "title": "Cell-specific mitochondrial affinity purification \\(CS-MAP) protocol",
    "content": [
        {
            "header": "Reagents",
            "content": "-NGM plates seeded with E. coli OP50 bacteria. \r\n\n\n-M9 Buffer \\[3 g KH2PO4, 6 g Na2HPO4, 5 g NaCl, 1 ml 1 M MgSO4, H2O to 1 litre. Sterilize by autoclaving.]. \r\n\n\n-MIB \\(Mitochondria Isolation Buffer 50 mM KCl, 110 mM mannitol, 70 mM sucrose, 0.1 mM EDTA \\(pH 8.0), 5 mM Tris-HCl \\(pH 7.4), supplemented with protease inhibitors \\(ref S8830, Sigma)).\r\n\n\n-PEB \\(1 x PBS, 2 mM EDTA, 1% BSA, protease inhibitors).\r\n\n\n-anti-HA \\(Influenza Hemagglutinin) magnetic beads \\(ref 88836, Pierce)."
        },
        {
            "header": "Equipment",
            "content": "-A 7 ml dounce homogenizer.\r\n\n\n-A homemade setup consisting of a column and a magnet \\(60 g neodymium)."
        },
        {
            "header": "Procedure",
            "content": "1- Grow approximately 10,000 worms on 2 x 150 mm NGM plates seeded with E. coli OP50 bacteria.\r\n\n\n2- Harvest worms and wash them 3 times with 15 ml of M9 buffer.\r\n\n\n3- Wash worms once with 15 ml of ddH2O.\r\n\n\n4- Resuspend worms in 3 ml of ice cold MIB and transfer them into a 7 ml dounce homogenizer on ice.\r\n\n\n5- Perform 21 gentle strokes.\r\n\n\n6- Centrifuge at 200 g for 5 min and keep supernatant.\r\n\n\n7- Centrifuge at 800 g for 10 min and keep supernatant.\r\n\n\n8- Centrifuge at high-speed 12,000 g for 10 min to pellet the total mitochondria.  \r\n\n\n 9- MIB is removed and replaced by 500 \u00b5l of ice cold PEB.\r\n\n\n10- Add 100 \u00b5g of anti-HA magnetic beads.\r\n\n\n11- Incubate samples at 4 \u00b0C for 1 h while rotating at 10 rpm.\r\n\n\n12- Transfer the samples on a homemade setup consisting of a column and a magnet.\r\n\n\n13- Ensure that beads were attracted to the side of the tip and held by the magnet and then wash twice with 25 ml of ice cold PEB. \r\n\n\n14- After washings, resuspend the beads in 20 \u00b5l of MIB."
        },
        {
            "header": "Timing",
            "content": "Approximately 2 hours"
        },
        {
            "header": "Troubleshooting",
            "content": "Do not let the bead dry out."
        },
        {
            "header": "Anticipated Results",
            "content": "Observation under a fluorescent microscope is used to confirm the presence of fluorescent mitochondria attached to beads."
        }
    ],
